<div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
  <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
    Concentration ranges of the ingredients
  </h1>
  <p class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">To tell us about the concentration ranges, you need to upload a PDF which lists the ingredients in the product.</p>
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
    What you need to tell us
  </h2>
  <p class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-3">List every ingredient in order of highest to lowest concentration range.</p>
  <p class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">
  For every ingredient in the product, you need to tell us the:
  </p>
  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>International Nomenclature of Cosmetic Ingredients (INCI) name, where available</li>
    <li>concentration ranges</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="govuk-inset-text">
    The National Poisons Information Service (NPIS) needs to know about some ingredients in the product â€“ list these first with the <strong>exact</strong> concentrations, in order of highest to lowest.
  </div>
</div>
<%= render 'ingredients_npis_needs_to_know' %>
<div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
  <p class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">For the other ingredients, list them in order of the highest to lowest concentration.</p>
  <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">
    Concentration ranges
  </h3>
  <p class="govuk-!-margin-bottom-1">Use these concentration ranges:</p>
  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
    <li>above 75% w/w up to 100% w/w</li>
    <li>above 50% w/w up to 75% w/w</li>
    <li>above 25% w/w up to 50% w/w</li>
    <li>above 10% w/w up to 25% w/w</li>
    <li>above 5% w/w up to 10% w/w</li>
    <li>above 1% w/w up to 5% w/w</li>
    <li>above 0.1% w/w up to 1% w/w</li>
    <li>up to and including 0.1% w/w</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    You must only include information about the ingredients in the product being notified. You must not upload complete assessment documents.
  </p>
</div>
